{"questionId":"9068444","questionHtml":"<p>A reaction proceeds by the following mechanism:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">step 1:&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math><br>step 2:&nbsp;<math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math></p>\n<p>Which rate equation is consistent with this mechanism?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp; Rate = <em>k</em>[B]<sup>2</sup>[C]</p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; Rate = <em>k</em>[A]<sup>2</sup>[B][C]</p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; Rate = <em>k</em>[A]<sup>2</sup></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; Rate = <em>k</em>[A][C]</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9068444","referenceCode":"21M.1.hl.TZ1.20","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"A reaction proceeds by the following mechanism: step 1: A+A→Bstep 2: B+C→D Which rate equation is consistent with this mechanism? A. Rate = k[B]2[C] B. Rate = k[A]2[B][C] C. Rate =","paper":"1","level":"hl","questionNumber":"20","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 16: Chemical kinetics","16.1 Rate expression and reaction mechanism","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 16: Chemical kinetics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}